(48, 1, '2018-10-02 03:54:08', '2018-10-02 03:54:08', '<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-46\" src=\"http://sn.elephantintheboardroom.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Capture-10-300x80.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"80\" />\r\n\r\nIn June 2018 The Australasian Corrosion Association held a series of two day workshops in Perth - Western Australia, Sydney - New South Wales and New Plymouth in New Zealand on the topic of Corrosion Under Insulation Prevention &amp; Mitigation.\r\n\r\nAs part of SN Integrity\'s commitment to support the Oil &amp; Gas Industry we were proud to be one of the two sponsors of this years workshops.\r\n\r\nThe two day workshop series in Perth, Sydney and New Plymouth was taught by international Corrosion Under Insulation (CUI) specialist and consultant Peter Bock from Houston, USA. Peter has over thirty years’ experience in elevated temperature coatings and CUI. He has published numerous articles on CUI issues, and has spoken at NACE, SSPC, ICC and other national and worldwide conferences regarding CUI problems and solutions. The workshop was dedicated to design, specification and inspection of corrosion control systems to prevent CUI in new or aged equipment covering causes of CUI, current state-of-the-art CUI coating systems, inspecting and evaluating aged CUI in the field, suitable CUI repair coating systems, and more.\r\n\r\nIf you\'re interested in sponsoring one of these events, visit their website <a href=\"https://events.corrosion.com.au/events/sponsorship-cui-prevention-mitigation-1-day-workshops/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'CUI Prevention and Mitigation June 2018', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '45-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-02 03:54:08', '2018-10-02 03:54:08', '', 45, 'http://sn.elephantintheboardroom.com.au/blog/2018/10/02/45-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(49, 1, '2018-10-02 03:58:35', '2018-10-02 03:58:35', 'The Oil &amp; Gas Technical Group provides a technical platform for the Oil &amp;amp; Gas Industries. The forum to discussed the latest developments and best practice in materials engineering, corrosion control in onshore and offshore environments.\r\n\r\nSpeakers and participants  shared their work and experiences from the Oil &amp;amp; Gas Industries.\r\n\r\n<strong>Guest Presenters:</strong>\r\n\r\nRob Morely – presented on Cryogenic CUI Inspection out of Shutdown.\r\n\r\nNestor Sequera – presented on Inspection Techniques to Detect Internal and External Corrosion on Insulated Piping\r\n\r\nBen Burrell – presented on Mitigating CUI Risk with Alkylated Amine Technology\r\n\r\nPhilip Fleming –  presented on Use of Vapor Phase Corrosion Inhibitors for Control of Corrosion Under Insulation (CUI)\r\n\r\nBarry Carson – presented on Mitigation of Corrosion Which Occurs Under All Insulation and Insulation Systems\r\n\r\nAdam Matthews – presented on Improvement in the corrosion protective property of the pure PIB system operating at temperature up to 120 deg C under insulation\r\n\r\nGraham Carlisle – presented on Liquid Applied Thermal Insulation Coatings: A Viable Option for the Prevention of CUI?\r\n\r\n<strong>Please find the presentations that are available from the above speakers at the event <a href=\"https://membership.corrosion.com.au/blog/detection-and-prevention-of-corrosion-in-the-oil-gas-industries-2/\">here</a>.</strong>', 'EVENT: Detection and Prevention of Corrosion in the Oil and Gas Industries', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'detection-and-prevention-of-corrosion-in-the-oil-and-gas-industries-event', '', '', '2018-10-03 02:22:07', '2018-10-03 02:22:07', '', 0, 'http://sn.elephantintheboardroom.com.au/blog/?p=49', 0, 'post', '', 0);
