(65, 1, '2018-10-03 06:13:32', '2018-10-03 06:13:32', '<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-46\" src=\"http://sn.elephantintheboardroom.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Capture-10-300x80.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"80\" />\r\n\r\nIn June 2018 The Australasian Corrosion Association held a series of two day workshops in Perth - Western Australia, Sydney - New South Wales and New Plymouth in New Zealand on the topic of Corrosion Under Insulation Prevention &amp; Mitigation.\r\n\r\nAs part of SN Integrity\'s commitment to support the Oil &amp; Gas Industry we were proud to be one of the two sponsors of this years workshops.\r\n\r\nThe two day workshop series in Perth, Sydney and New Plymouth was taught by international Corrosion Under Insulation (CUI) specialist and consultant Peter Bock from Houston, USA. Peter has over thirty years’ experience in elevated temperature coatings and CUI. He has published numerous articles on CUI issues, and has spoken at NACE, SSPC, ICC and other national and worldwide conferences regarding CUI problems and solutions. The workshop was dedicated to design, specification and inspection of corrosion control systems to prevent CUI in new or aged equipment covering causes of CUI, current state-of-the-art CUI coating systems, inspecting and evaluating aged CUI in the field, suitable CUI repair coating systems, and more.\r\n\r\nIf you\'re interested in sponsoring one of these events, visit their website <a href=\"https://events.corrosion.com.au/events/sponsorship-cui-prevention-mitigation-1-day-workshops/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'EVENT: CUI Prevention and Mitigation June 2018', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '45-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-10-03 06:13:32', '2018-10-03 06:13:32', '', 45, 'http://sn.elephantintheboardroom.com.au/blog/2018/10/03/45-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
